Audit PostgreSQL 8.X and 9.X configuration

Must be run from root

Usage:
  ./postgresql.sh -h

Options:
  -c|--conf : Specify where the main configuration files lie. /etc/postgresql/9.X/main by default
  -o|--out  : Specify where the script should store its results. $PWD/results by default
  -b|--bin  : Specify the psql binary path. $(which psql) by default
